-Samuel Allen
2/16/2020

snippet.textDisplay:
This video just had me dripping real tears 😥 I packed my basketball memories so far down that even when I thought about it I wouldn't pull out even a small portion of the memories as this video just pulled out. That was me frfr I didn't go anywhere without my ball. That park remind me of seabrook and could b since he from fayetteville. I remember visiting my dad for the summers and every day walkin up and down that hill after crossing ramsey or from wherever he moved when i visited.

I remember as a 15 or 16 and beatin a college player from fsu, i usually play in rain but it was raining way too hard that day or something, and me bein me said maybe it's open lol the janitor or someone caught me hoopin and said i don't suppose to be n there but anytime it rain i could. A lil after a player came in and played 1 on 1, and that's when i did what i usually do and kept beating him in a game of 5 til I'm shirts off drippin sweat and he finally gave up and didn't say run it back anymore.

Fayetteville, my hometown, anywhere i kept a basketball and a library card. Man yall had me unpack some memories with this one. I went the wrong way, but I take accountability and full responsibility, nobody fault but mine.
